Questions asked in Review-1:
1)If your system is deployed internationally and experiences crashes or performance failures, what measures have you planned to ensure reliability, scalability, and maintenance? 
A) If the system is deployed internationally and experiences crashes or performance failures, reliability can be ensured through cloud-based infrastructure such as Amazon Web Services or Microsoft Azure. Load balancing and auto-scaling help manage high traffic efficiently. Regular data backups and disaster recovery plans prevent data loss. Real-time monitoring tools detect issues early and reduce downtime. A microservices architecture with global support teams ensures smooth maintenance and scalability.
2)What types of complaints are typically handled in a campus maintenance system?
A)A campus maintenance system typically handles complaints related to infrastructure, electrical faults, plumbing issues, and IT problems. It also manages housekeeping concerns and sanitation issues across the campus. Equipment-related complaints such as elevator or air conditioning failures are included. Security-related issues like CCTV malfunction or poor lighting are also reported. Overall, it covers all facility and maintenance-related concerns within the campus.
3)What role does user authentication play in complaint management?
A)User authentication ensures that only authorized users can access the complaint management system. It verifies the identity of students, staff, and administrators before allowing actions. This helps maintain data security and prevents fake or duplicate complaints. Authentication also enables role-based access control for different user types. Additionally, it ensures accountability by tracking user activities within the system.
4)What notification mechanisms can be integrated into the system?
A)Notification mechanisms improve communication between users and maintenance teams. Email notifications can confirm complaint submission and provide status updates. SMS alerts can be used for urgent or high-priority issues. Mobile app push notifications offer real-time updates to users. Escalation alerts notify supervisors if complaints are not resolved on time.
